:PNLGRP.
.**********************************************************************
.* General help
.**********************************************************************
:HELP name='TDV5110'
WIDTH='74'
DEPTH='21'.
Helptext for Schedule Information Request
:P.
Use this display to send a FIR "Schedule Information Request"
and receive a FIA "Schedule Information Answer".
:H3.Message Function
:UL.
:LI.
To request Schedule Information
(on direct flights and connections of up to three flights)
for a specific routing on either a specific
date or for a period of a month.
:EUL.
:P.
Information that must be entered is highlighted.
Press F10 to send the request.
:P.
In order to limit the volume of information to be
transmitted in the Answer Message, optional data
elements may be included in the Request Message.
:P.
The matrix below illustrates the possible combinations:
:FIG.
Request  ICAO    Earliest  Latest   Connection   Aircraft
         Carrier Departure Arrival  Restriction  Possibility
         Code    Time      Date/Time             Code
For a     X        X          X          X         X
date
For a     X        -          -          X         X
month
:FIGCAP. X means that the element can be used,
- means that the element can't be used.
:EFIG.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5111'.Requested Routing - Help
:XH3.Requested Routing
:P.
This information is mandatory. Fill out both the
Airport/City Code (of Origin) and the
Airport/City Code (of Destination).
:P.
The Airport/City Code is a Coded representation
of a specific airport/city code.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5112'.Date or Month - Help
:XH3.Date or Month
:P.
The month is mandatory and the day is optional.
:P.
When a Day of Month is not specified, flights
are being requested for a specific month.
:P.
When a Day of Month is specified, flights
are being requested for a specific date.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5113'.ICAO Carrier Code - Help
:XH3.ICAO Carrier Code
:P.
Coded Identification approved by ICAO for a carrier
:P.
When a Carrier Code is not specified, flights
are being requested for all carriers.
:P.
When a Carrier Code is specified, flights
are being requested for that carrier only.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5114'.Earliest Departure Time - Help
:XH3.Earliest Departure Time
:P.
When an Earliest Departure Time is not specified,
The flights (or first flight in case of combinations)
being requested are those departing from 00h00.
:P.
When an Earliest Departure Time is specified,
The flights (or first flight in case of combinations)
being requested are those departing from the specified time.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5115'.Latest Arrival Date/Time - Help
:XH3.Latest Arrival Date/Time
:P.
When a Latest Arrival Date/Time is not specified,
all flights are being requested.
:P.
When a Latest Arrival Date is specified, and a
Latest Arrival Time is not specified, the
flights (or last flight in case of combinations)
being requested are those that arrive at the
destination no later than 23h59 on the
specified date.
:P.
When both the Latest Arrival Date and Time is specified,
the flights (or last flight in case of combinations)
being requested are those that arrive at the
destination no later than the specified date and time.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5116'
WIDTH='74'
DEPTH='21'.
Connection restriction - Help
:XH3.Connection Restriction
:P.
The various possible combinations of connections requested are precised
in the matrix below:
:FIG.
Connection   Airport  City Code  Connection Requested
Restriction  Code
Indicator
   -          -           -      All Connections Requested
   N          -           -      No Connections Requested
   L          X           -      Only the Connections via
                                 this airport are requested
   L          -           X      Only the Connections via
                                 this city are requested
   E          X           -      All Connections requested
                                 except those via this airport
   E          -           X      All Connections requested
                                 except those via this city
:FIGCAP.Note that Airport/City code can only be entered
if Connection Restriction Indicator is L or E.
:EFIG.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5117'.Aircraft Possibility Code - Help
:XH3.Aircraft Possibility Code
:P.
Code Indicating the transportation possibilities
of an aircraft.
:P.
When an Aircraft Possibility Code is not specified,
flights being requested include all aircraft possibilities.
:P.
When an Aircraft Possibility Code is specified,
flights being requested are limited to that
aircraft possibility code.
:P.
The Aircraft Possibility Codes are specified below:
:DL.
:DT.
BBQ
:DD.
Mixed configuration (Combi) aircraft carrying Loose Load Cargo
on the passenger deck.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
LLQ
:DD.
Mixed configuration (Combi) aircraft carrying Containerized
Cargo (ULDs) on the passenger deck.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
LPQ
:DD.
Mixed configuration (Combi) aircraft carrying Containerized
(ULDs)/Palletized Cargo on the passenger deck.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
PPQ
:DD.
Mixed configuration aircraft carrying
Palletized Cargo on the passenger deck.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
PPJ
:DD.
Passenger flight operated by wide-bodied aircraft
carrying palletized Cargo.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
LLJ
:DD.
Passenger flight operated by wide-bodied aircraft
carrying Containerized (ULDs).
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
LPJ
:DD.
Passenger flight operated by wide-bodied aircraft
carrying Containerized (ULDs)/Palletized Cargo.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
LPF
:DD.
Pure freighter flight carrying
Containerized (ULDs)/Palletized Cargo.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
BBF
:DD.
Pure freighter flight carrying
Loose Load Cargo.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
LLF
:DD.
Pure freighter flight carrying
Containerized Cargo (ULDs).
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
PPF
:DD.
Pure freighter flight carrying
Palletized Cargo.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
LLV
:DD.
Truck carrying Containerized Cargo (ULDs).
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
LPV
:DD.
Truck carrying Containerized (ULDs)/Palletized Cargo.
:EDL.
:DL.
:DT.
BBV
:DD.
Truck carrying Loose Load Cargo.
:EDL.
