:EDL.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5140'.
No Answer Details - Help
:XH3.No Answer Details
:P.
The Answer did not contain specific Schedule Answer.
Because of that it's not possible to present possible choices.
The Answer received may either be an error message, or
there is no schedule available, or the answer is presented
in a compressed form as an answer to an request for
a month without a specified day.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5160'.
Answer Details - Help
:XH3.Answer Details
:P.
The top of the screen contains the request detail
as the participant has read it.
All fields will not necesarry contain a value.
:P.
The lower part of the display will contain an list
of possible routings to select.
The routings shown can be of different types.
Either it's a direct routing from/to the requested
airport/city or it can be several routings with a number
of connections. SYSPED400 can only handel 3 flights in a routing.
Fill out the option field with 1,2,3 to select flight(s) to
the routing in the airwaybill format. The numbers 1,2,3
will also indicate where the flight will be put in
the format for the airwaybill.
:EHELP.
:HELP name='TDV5199'.
Function keys - Help
:XH3.Function keys
:P.
:XH3.F1=Help
:P.
Can be used insted of HELP in all formats.
:P.
:XH3.F3=Exit
:P.
Ends the program.
:P.
:XH3.F4=Display List
:P.
Not in function
:XH3.F9=Select new part. ID
:P.
F9 can be used to select a new participant to which you can send
the FIR
:XH3.F10=Send Request
:P.
F10 is used to transmit the Schedule Information Request
:EHELP.
:EPNLGRP.
